menu "breadboard: bb_health"

config BB_HEALTH_AUTOREGISTER
    bool "Auto-register /api/health HTTP route via bb_init"
    default y
    help
        When enabled, bb_health self-registers GET /api/health through bb_init.
        Disable to keep the bb_health_register_extender API but skip the route
        entirely.

config BB_HEALTH_STACK_POLL_MS
    int "Stack high-water monitor poll interval (ms)"
    default 10000
    range 1000 3600000
    help
        How often the stack high-water monitor checks all FreeRTOS task
        stack margins. Default 10 000 ms (10 s) is a low-overhead poll
        that catches margin erosion well before a real overflow.

        Note: the monitor requires CONFIG_FREERTOS_USE_TRACE_FACILITY=y
        (enabled automatically by FREERTOS_GENERATE_RUN_TIME_STATS or
        similar; check your sdkconfig). If TRACE_FACILITY is off, the
        monitor compiles as a no-op and this setting has no effect.

        Strongly recommended: also set
          CONFIG_FREERTOS_CHECK_STACKOVERFLOW_PTRVAL=y
        (CONFIG_FREERTOS_CHECK_STACKOVERFLOW=2) so a real overflow prints
        an attributable task-name message instead of a silent abort.

config BB_HEALTH_STACK_LOW_BYTES
    int "Stack low-water threshold (bytes)"
    default 256
    range 64 65536
    help
        Free stack bytes below which a task is flagged as low. This is a
        near-overflow danger threshold: a task within ~256 B (64 words) of
        overflowing its stack. The old default of 512 B over-warned because
        fixed-depth system tasks (ipc0, ipc1, bb_log_writer) normally run
        at ~500 B high-water and are not in danger. 256 B fires only when
        a task is genuinely close to overflow. Still tunable via
        CONFIG_BB_HEALTH_STACK_LOW_BYTES.

        The monitor posts a health.stack event on the first poll where a
        task crosses below this threshold (transition into low), not on
        every poll, to avoid spamming the event bus.

        uxTaskGetStackHighWaterMark returns words; the monitor multiplies
        by sizeof(StackType_t) (4 on Xtensa/RISC-V 32-bit) to get bytes.

config BB_HEALTH_STACK_MAX_TASKS
    int "Max FreeRTOS tasks tracked in stack debounce table"
    range 8 256
    default 32
    help
        Maximum number of FreeRTOS tasks the stack high-water monitor can
        track simultaneously in its per-task debounce table. Tasks seen
        beyond this limit are silently skipped (no low-stack event will
        fire for them). Default 32 covers typical breadboard firmware
        configurations; raise on boards with many user tasks.

config BB_HEALTH_STACK_AUTOSTART
    bool "Auto-start the stack high-water monitor timer at PRE_HTTP"
    default y
    depends on FREERTOS_USE_TRACE_FACILITY
    help
        When enabled, bb_health_stack_monitor_start (the periodic stack
        high-water poll timer) self-registers at the bb_init PRE_HTTP tier.
        Disable to call bb_health_stack_monitor_start manually before
        bb_health_stack_monitor_init.

config BB_HEALTH_AUTO_ATTACH
    bool "Auto-attach health.stack to /api/events"
    default y
    depends on BB_EVENT_ROUTES_AUTOREGISTER
    help
        When enabled, bb_health's stack monitor attaches the "health.stack"
        topic to the bb_event_routes SSE stream so /api/events surfaces it
        without an explicit consumer call. Disable if you want the bb_event
        topic for internal subscribers only.

endmenu
